#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME.rst:2
msgid "CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME.rst:4
msgid ""
"The name of the operating system for which CMake is to build. See the :"
"variable:`CMAKE_SYSTEM_VERSION` variable for the OS version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME.rst:7
msgid ""
"Note that ``CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME`` is not set to anything by default when "
"running in script mode, since it's not building anything."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME.rst:11
msgid "System Name for Host Builds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME.rst:13
msgid ""
"``CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME`` is by default set to the same value as the :variable:"
"`CMAKE_HOST_SYSTEM_NAME` variable so that the build targets the host system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME.rst:18
msgid "System Name for Cross Compiling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../variable/CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME.rst:20
msgid ""
"``CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME`` may be set explicitly when first configuring a new "
"build tree in order to enable :ref:`cross compiling <Cross Compiling "
"Toolchain>`. In this case the :variable:`CMAKE_SYSTEM_VERSION` variable must "
"also be set explicitly."
msgstr ""

